This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with multi-object tracking in videos. It also involves machine learning techniques for learning target-specific similarities, which makes it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the use of global optimization algorithms and network flow models suggests that it could also be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) categories. Finally, the paper deals with the robustness of the tracking system, which could make it relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
